ROCm is a brand name for the ROCm open software platform (for software)
or the ROCm open platform ecosystem (includes hardware like FPGAs or
other CPU architectures).

Radeon Open Compute Thunk Interface

This is the user-mode API interfaces used to interact with the ROCk
driver.

Starting from the 1.7 release, ROCt uses drm render device. This requires
the user to belong to video group.

Add the user account to video group with

# usermod -a -G video username

if the user is not part of video group yet. 
